quest_1_2.CompleteDesc: Life in the Astra Shelter is peaceful enough. There's Shirli, Mi-a, and a very friendly crowd. I've already fallen in love with the place. Maybe I can really take it easy here for a while.
quest_1_2.ProgressDesc: Astra Shelter is unfamiliar to me. Zeke and Shirli took an unconscious me in, yet I can't recall anything before that, except a feeling of unease. What happened? I'll have to look into it...

quest_1_1_2.UnActiveDesc: Complete "Resolve Crisis" main mission to unlock
quest_1_1_2.CompleteDesc: If we got there sooner, maybe we could've saved Una. Her sacrifice will forever be in our memory.
quest_1_1_2.ProgressDesc: Find Detective Comez by the Astra Shelter gate

quest_1_3.CompleteDesc: I heard Heirs of Aida are a cult of zealots, but that woman claimed they could save Shirli. Can there be hope for Shirli, after all?
quest_1_3.ProgressDesc: No one knows what danger lies in that mysterious ruin, so no wonder Zeke got angry. Maybe I should convince Shirli to sit down with Zeke and have a heart-to-heart.

quest_1_2_2.UnActiveDesc: Complete "Resolve Crisis" main mission to unlock
quest_1_2_2.CompleteDesc: The shelter should be safer under the Omnium Guard's protection.
quest_1_2_2.ProgressDesc: Find Alfred the programmer in Astra Shelter

quest_1_4.CompleteDesc: I didn't find any clues to their whereabouts in the ruin, except for more incoherent information from an ancient smart servant, such as Chrono Chambers and the First Regression... What secrets lie in the past?
quest_1_4.ProgressDesc: The mystery woman who took Zeke and Shirli is probably not a friend... Finding them is the priority. The coordinates in the abandoned lab were the key to decoding the ruin's location. I'm going for leads to their trails.

quest_1_5.CompleteDesc: New twists in the development: Zeke's identity, my rigged suppressor, and the crisis in Hykros... There's a much larger plot behind all this.
quest_1_5.ProgressDesc: The Omnium Towers' sudden activation isn't coincidental. Franz suggested I come to Hykros to learn more, and possibly find out Shirli and Zeke's whereabouts.

quest_1_6.CompleteDesc: After some struggle, we finally turned off the Omnium Tower in Astra. But it's only the start of a journey involving the towers and the Tower of Fantasy.
quest_1_6.ProgressDesc: Zeke and that mystery woman probably got something to do with the Omnium Tower. I decided to help Hykros shut it down, hopefully finding Zeke and Shirli while at it.

quest_2_2.CompleteDesc: Banges is livelier than I imagined. My luck held up as I met an enthusiastic guide, Hilda, and got to make friends with Kolador and his son Theo over Graceday, and surprisingly uncovered Zeke's track.
quest_2_2.ProgressDesc: The incident in Astra has come to an end. Although the tower is shut off, I didn't find anything more on Zeke and Shirli. With optimism, I set off for the next Omnium Tower in Banges.

quest_2_1_2.UnActiveDesc: Complete "Kill Enemies" main mission to unlock
quest_2_1_2.CompleteDesc: Facing the Heirs' siege, Jason chose mutual destruction by detonation. No matter what is behind Omnium and the world, his determination has brought a ray of hope to the darkness of this world.
quest_2_1_2.ProgressDesc: Find Coatl in Banges Port and complete the following mission

quest_2_3.CompleteDesc: Heirs of Aida again... what do those lunatics want now? They probably have the Astrum, and President Kolador and Theo are missing too. I got no time to waste!
quest_2_3.ProgressDesc: The Banges HQ was raided! I must rescue President Kolador and Theo.

quest_2_2_2.UnActiveDesc: Complete "Day Break" main mission to unlock
quest_2_2_2.CompleteDesc: I met a young man who follows the Heirs of Aida out in the field. He believed Omnium was nothing more than a tool Hykros used to oppose and rule the Aidans. The Heirs realized the truth and are the ones to save us.
quest_2_2_2.ProgressDesc: Found Vincent in the shelter at south Banges

quest_2_4.CompleteDesc: The situation is more complicated than I thought. President Kolador and Theo apparently weren't abducted by the Heirs of Aida. Hopkins in the black market seems to hold critical information, but it won't be easy getting it out of that shady dealer.
quest_2_4.ProgressDesc: Franz provided me with valuable clues. The Heirs' influence has spread throughout areas neighboring Banges. I must investigate each one and leave no stone unturned.

quest_2_5.CompleteDesc: They're wrong, they're all wrong... Blind love only brings tragedies like this. It should've never been this way...
quest_2_5.ProgressDesc: After negotiations, Hopkins finally told me where to find the Astrum. The truth is close at hand. I can't stop, no matter what awaits me ahead.

quest_2_6.CompleteDesc: I hope the people here can soon leave the sorrow behind, but I must move on to a new journey. Franz told me Zeke and "Number Two" went to Cetus Island, the mystery park hovering over Navia.
quest_2_6.ProgressDesc: Theo's passing is pure tragedy. President Kolador paid for his misguided judgment, but I have little time to mourn, as I have another task I must do—turning off the second Omnium Tower.

quest_3_2.CompleteDesc: I haphazardly uncovered a joint plot between the Hyenas and the Ravagers, and saved smart servant Melo of Cetus Island. However, those mob wrecked the dirigible, so I must find another way to reach the island.
quest_3_2.ProgressDesc: I don't know much about Navia and Cetus Island. I wonder what kind of person that the mysterious Dr. Claire, owner of the park, will turn out to be.

quest_3_1_2.UnActiveDesc: Complete "Return Trip" main mission to unlock
quest_3_1_2.CompleteDesc: Hanna picked up a peculiar correspondence signal and asked you to investigate.
quest_3_1_2.ProgressDesc: Find Hanna at Cetus Island and help her.

quest_3_3.CompleteDesc: Hanna seemed much more clever than Melo. With their help, we retrieved the dirigible and reached the island, where to my surprise, I ran into Zeke. What are they doing here?
quest_3_3.ProgressDesc: Black Dog admitted they have another base where they kept another smart servant named Hanna, and a dirigible for us to get on the island. I'm going to try my luck there.

quest_3_2_2.UnActiveDesc: Complete "Return Trip" main mission to unlock
quest_3_2_2.ProgressDesc: Find Slayer on Cetus Island and help him.

quest_3_4.CompleteDesc: Poor Shirli... So the hope that woman mentioned was mechanic modifications? Have you ever pondered whether that's what Shirli wanted, Zeke?
quest_3_4.ProgressDesc: Dr. Claire's... guest, is indeed Zeke. What is he doing here, though? Regardless, I have to know what is it between him and the Heirs!

quest_3_5.CompleteDesc: What did Black Dog steal from the Cetus Island to get the doctor so worked up...? Never mind, let's get the device back first!
quest_3_5.ProgressDesc: Zeke took Shirli with him and I'm stuck with the mess! The doctor wants me to work it off. God knows how long that will take... Never mind, I'll do as she said, since I still need help from the doctor.

quest_3_6.CompleteDesc: I can't believe Black Dog stole a Chrono Switch. So Dr. Claire has been researching time retracement? And who is Luhn? The mystery just keeps getting more complicated...
quest_3_6.ProgressDesc: That Black Dog can't do anything right except run away! The doctor sounded stressed, so the device must be important. Maybe I can retrieve it and clear my obligations with her once and for all.

quest_4_2.CompleteDesc: The top priority right now is turning off the Omnium Tower in Crown Mines, but it has been hit with a rather peculiar pandemic lately.
quest_4_2.ProgressDesc: The truth behind Omnium is more shocking than I imagined. The application of time retracement is indeed an issue to ponder.

quest_4_1_2.CompleteDesc: Having foresight means you know some things cannot be changed, but it also means you know some things can be. That's the gist of the notes Luhn left.
quest_4_1_2.ProgressDesc: Gus found something unusual in the mines. Find Gus in Crown Mines Transport Hub and help him.

quest_4_3.CompleteDesc: The Hyenas robbed the shipment of medicine. But the miners finally stopped striking. Get ready to see Mr. Kim with Giggs.
quest_4_3.ProgressDesc: The miners are on strike over the pandemic, and Foreman Giggs seems to have run into trouble. Help him out.

quest_4_2_2.UnActiveDesc: Available after the main mission "Angry Mob"
quest_4_2_2.CompleteDesc: See, this is reality. It's enough to just survive.
quest_4_2_2.ProgressDesc: There's suddenly a rumor about the Lumina being haunted at the mines. Could it be the Heirs of Aida who are behind this? There may be some clues at the parliament (406,306).

quest_4_4.CompleteDesc: Got the Astrum after defeating the Hyena Queen with Dr. Hamlin's help. Give it to the doctor to study the secret of Omnium and Astrum for now.
quest_4_4.ProgressDesc: Turning off the Omnium Tower requires Astrum, but Mr. Kim's Astrum is stolen. There's also trouble brewing in the mine. Mr. Kim promises you the Astrum, but you must solve the problems in the mines.

quest_4_5.CompleteDesc: It turns out Giggs has a secret deal with the Heirs of Aida, but the liar was rescued by his co-conspirators after a distraction.
quest_4_5.ProgressDesc: Mr. Franz has come to the mines to investigate Heirs activities. It seems either Mr. Kim or Giggs made a secret pact with the Heirs...

quest_4_6.CompleteDesc: So Giggs and the Heirs have been nabbing miners in Area 4 for experiments, and the radiation is what started the pandemic. But does Mr. Kim really not know anything about it?
quest_4_6.ProgressDesc: Mr. Kim revealed that Area 4 is where the medicine is actually researched and produced, and a force shield seals off the passage. Guess there're a lot of secrets in there...

quest_5_2.CompleteDesc: The Omnium Towers have been deactivated, but strange things are still happening all over.
quest_5_2.ProgressDesc: Threats lurk everywhere in this icy land.

quest_5_1_2.UnActiveDesc: Available after the main mission "Break into Aarniel Fortress"
quest_5_1_2.CompleteDesc: The new detectors have all been deployed. Hopefully the Snowfield Expedition will be able to operate more safely now.
quest_5_1_2.ProgressDesc: Conan of the expedition team needs your help.

quest_5_3.CompleteDesc: We found a coded manuscript belonging to the Heirs of Aida. Maybe Dr. Claire can help me decipher it?
quest_5_3.ProgressDesc: The news I got from Hykros is so worrying. I wonder how my friends in Astra are doing.

quest_5_2_2.UnActiveDesc: Available after the main mission "Break into Aarniel Fortress"
quest_5_2_2.ProgressDesc: Find Melo on Cetus Island and help him.

quest_5_4.CompleteDesc: All clues point to The Lumina. Hopefully, things can finally be put to rest there.
quest_5_4.ProgressDesc: The doctor is missing, and the smart servants are acting weird too. What happened on Cetus Island?

quest_5_5.CompleteDesc: It seems the problem lies in the Warren Snowfield. I should take Zeke back to the shelter first to have his wounds treated.
quest_5_5.ProgressDesc: These ruins are littered with ships from a long-lost age. I wonder what lies hidden within?

quest_5_6.CompleteDesc: I finally rescued Shirli and, after cutting off the power, discovered the location of a large Heirs of Aida encampment: Aarniel Fortress.
quest_5_6.ProgressDesc: The secrets of the Heirs will finally be revealed, but we need to hurry!

quest_6_2.CompleteDesc: The Sage has already retreated from Aarniel Fortress. The situation is quickly growing out of control...
quest_6_2.ProgressDesc: Aarniel Fortress: A massive Heirs of Aida encampment. I need to hurry and find Shirli and Zeke.

quest_6_3.CompleteDesc: The road to the Tower of Fantasy is now open, but the next step requires that I proceed on my own...
quest_6_3.ProgressDesc: The ruined city surrounding the Tower of Fantasy... The Heirs of Aida have already entered the Tower; I have to find Franz before anything else.

quest_6_4.CompleteDesc: After countless hardships, I finally have a chance to see this mysterious person with my own two eyes.
quest_6_4.ProgressDesc: After entering the Tower of Fantasy, I came across a mysterious person...

quest_6_5.CompleteDesc: This time, it was Zeke who saved Shirli... Could all of this be fate?
quest_6_5.ProgressDesc: Who is responsible for all of this chaos, Shirli or the Sage?

quest_6_6.CompleteDesc: Franz and Elric are both here; it seems Dr. Claire has made a new discovery.
quest_6_6.ProgressDesc: It's been several months since that terrible battle...
